Rashad Jennings Dances to Bruno Mars on DWTS DWTS: Bruno Mars Would Be Proud of Rashad Jennings For His "24K Magic" Cha-Cha March 20, 2017 163 Shares Chat with us on Facebook Messenger. Learn what's trending across POPSUGAR. 
Dancing With the Stars kicked off on Monday night, and NFL running back Rashad Jennings helped open the 24th season with a cha-cha to very fitting "24K Magic" by Bruno Mars. Jennings and partner Emma Slater sauntered all over the dance floor, and their routine earned them a standing ovation and one of the highest scores of the night â€” after Simone Biles, that is. Take a look, catch Normani Kordei's quickstep , and get psyched for another fabulous season!
